    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok so if i get a kit, what should i look for specifically? like is there a way to tell if something is actively stripping the nutrients away before the plant even gets them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Look for a clear indicator scale on your testing kit to see if your pH is too acidic or too alkaline for tomatoes. Nutrient lockout happens when the soil pH is outside the ideal range, preventing even present nutrients from being available to the roots. If the pH is significantly off, you can correct it by adding agricultural lime to raise the pH or elemental sulfur to lower it.",
      "source": "target",
